Patient: What kind of food should I be eating with heart failure?
Healthcare Educator: Eat plenty of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins. Limit salt and processed foods.

Patient: Can I eat canned vegetables?
Healthcare Educator: Canned vegetables often have added salt. Pick low-sodium versions or fresh ones if possible.

Patient: What about fast food? It's cheap and easy to get.
Healthcare Educator: Fast food often has a lot of salt and fat. Try to cook at home using fresh ingredients.

Patient: I don't have much time to cook. Any suggestions?
Healthcare Educator: Prepare meals in bulk on weekends. Freeze them and heat up when needed.

Patient: What if I don't have a freezer?
Healthcare Educator: Choose simple recipes with fresh ingredients. Beans, rice and vegetables take little time to cook.